  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Evidence carries explicitly low confidence (~50%) arising from limited experimental replicates and wide uncertainty bounds on blood rheology inputs; these limitations are documented honestly with full rationale. A sensitivity analysis confirms that inlet viscosity and hematocrit variation are the dominant drivers of output uncertainty. The decision accepts the package at medium assurance because: (1) the relative hemolysis index criterion is conservative, (2) physical testing provides an independent safety net, and (3) the sensitivity analysis bounds the worst-case deviation within the regulatory acceptance threshold.",
